Question
10:
Real-World Summary Question (Exam-Perfect)
Question
Explain with an example how vectors, lists, and data frames are used in a real-world application.
Answer
Vector stores homogeneous data (marks, prices)
List stores heterogeneous data (profiles)
Data Frame stores structured tabular data (records)
scores <- c(85, 90, 88)
profile <- list(
Name = "Gayathri",
Age = 21,
Scores = scores
 
)
records <- data.frame(
Subject = c("Math", "CS", "Physics"),
Marks = scores
)
